<font color="#FF0000">THERE BACK!!!!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov  8  8:49:03 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
  The war has changed my life. It all came down to one second in one day boom, the world is not the same. Have tried very hard to put myself back together since then but the pieces don't seem to fit anymore. <br>
  Lately, there has been the urge to walk away from everybody and eveything. To hide in drugs, booze, sex,travel,and street life. The nightmares, intrusive thoughts, anger, depression, have all come back . What do I do with these feelings ? The pain , sorrow, all I want to do is get numb and hide from me. <br>
  Relationships,a joke, think I want a squad buddy more than a woman. If there is less than total trust I feel that I can't depend on anyone, like my life depends on it. Just ended a relationship, another one bites the dust. Often wonder if it's the PTSD or if that's just the way I am.<br>
  Prayer has seemed to help in the past, but anymore it's as though I'm talking to wet cardboard. Feel like a cold, cold wind is blowing through my soul.<br>
  I've been taugh in counciling to keep going no matter what, that life will change, will get better, but the old behavoirs are back. Or sometimes you eat the bear,sometimes the bear eats you. <br>
        Happy Veterans Day,<br>
             Michael
<p><code>--   (Michael) </code><p>


